    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>“Move around. Don’t stay in one hole all day.”</strong> Covering water increases your odds.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>“Pack multiple setups.”</strong> Conditions can shift rapidly; having bait, lures, and flies gives you options.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>“Watch water clarity.”</strong> Ideal clarity is 2–4 feet for most rivers.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>“Talk to others.”</strong> Friendly anglers are often willing to share tips and successful methods.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    By learning from those who fish these rivers regularly, you'll increase your odds of landing that prized steelhead.
